Great recommendations for nearby food, everything you need in the kitchen, including Keurig OR standard drip coffee options. The downstairs game room was a lot of fun. Great spot to spend down time. There are convenience/liquor stores no more than a 15 min walk away, and plenty of delivery options as well. If I were ever in GB again with a small group, I would definitely try booking this again. Tracy also went above-and-beyond in securing a portable chess set that we could play outside.
Thanks again for everything Tracy!

Of course, the stadium is just a mile away, and the mall is not much farther. Overall, the "Little House" is a great place to spend with a couple of kids, and I wouldn't hesitate to rebook.

Tracy's house came as advertised, and exceeded expectations! My friend and I traveled to Green Bay to experience an authentic game day, Lambeau experience! Tracy's house more than helped us fulfill that experience. The house was perfectly situated in a quiet neighborhood within a pleasant walking distance to the stadium and provided a great 'home base' for us for the weekend.
Tracy was extremely easy to coordinate with, making the check in/out process simple and seamless. The beds were extremely comfortable and allowed us to rest up and expend maximum energy watching the game!
As an avid football fan, I've always heard that you should attend a game in Green Bay. I can now attest to that sentiment, and can also say, stay at Tracy's house if you're looking for the true Lambeau neighborhood experience. Even though my beloved Patriots lost, I couldn't have asked for a better experience or a better place to stay.

Having a bonfire pit is always a nice touch to me, but it was extra helpful that Jody had some things to help us start the fire along with wood.
Not only did I appreciate the interior of the home, but I wanted to shout of the exterior too! Sure, it is cute, but also having that bright yellow door really helped with finding the place! lol.
Luckily, I had no issues and was in no need to contact Jody, but between the airbnb message system and by providing her phone number she also made it very comfortable to contact her should something come up- which I highly appreciated.
Thanks again so much for the stay. If we ever find ourselves in Green Bay again, I know where to go.

My only complaint was a total lack of snow removal during a 2 day winter storm which resulted in me having to shovel the driveway each day before and after working 12 hour shifts. The area received 6+ inches each day so it was impossible to get out or back in without clearing the driveway. The owner stated his regular plow guy was on vacation and his college age back up was on spring break. The owner did offer to pay for an uber but I was not confident I would be able to book a ride after work given the weather conditions so I declined. A snow removal company did arrive around 1am on the second day but only cleared the sidewalks as I had already shoveled the driveway upon my return home that evening.
